cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.CC

This paper deals with the extension of First-order Logic (FOL) using intensional abstraction operator, which is a topic related to logic and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses algebraic structures and their interpretations, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the Tarski's interpretation of the standard extensional FOL, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
